  "text": "Pregnancy-associated depression in cell-mediated immunity may be due to alterations in hormonal and serum factors as well as to a decrease in the ratio of T helper to suppressor cells during pregnancy [CITATION_1] . In addition, the local placental suppression of cell-mediated immunity necessary to prevent maternal rejection of the placenta may contribute to susceptibility of the fetus to infection with listeriosis [CITATION_2] .",
